## Case Definition
## Confirmed Case
## Laboratory confirmation of infection:
- Identification of rotavirus in stool(A) by electron microscopy, enzyme immunoassay (EIA), latex agglutination or molecular
methods when available
## Probable Case (Outbreak Only)
Clinical illness(B) in a person who is epidemiologically linked to a confirmed case
(A) Refer to the Public Health Laboratory (ProvLab) Guide to Services for current specimen collection and submission information.
(B) Clinical illness is characterized by fever, emesis, watery diarrhea and sometimes associated with dehydration, especially in young children.

## Reporting Requirements
Laboratories
All laboratories shall report all positive laboratory results by mail, fax or electronic transfer within 48 hours (two business days)
to the:
- Chief Medical Officer of Health (or designate), and
- Medical Officer of Health (or designate) of the zone.
Alberta Health Services and First Nations and Inuit Health Branch
- Laboratory surveillance only except in the event of an outbreak. Completion of a Notifiable Disease Report is not required.
- Report outbreaks only using the Alberta Outbreak Report Form.

